 :tx/rationale "DESIGN: Dynamic AGENTS.md as Live Store Projection. Current AGENTS.md is static — same instructions regardless of store state. The braid-seed section is dynamic but only covers WHAT to work on, not HOW to work. The methodology layer (adaptive ceremony, provenance requirements, gap awareness) is static prose that agents read once and forget under k* pressure. Solution: generate_agent_md produces a methodology section ADAPTED to current store state. It includes: (1) current methodology gaps from methodology_gaps(), (2) adaptive ceremony protocol with current k* level, (3) top-3 R(t) actions pre-computed (no need to run braid next), (4) session-specific constraints (which subsystems exist, which don't), (5) provenance chain requirement. This turns static methodology prose into a LIVE PROJECTION — the same transformation that seed applies to context, applied to methodology. The infrastructure exists: generate_agent_md in agent_md.rs, GuidanceContext, methodology_gaps. ~50 LOC wiring."
